                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-395" type="surname" value="MENZIES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-395" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MENZIES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am master-tailor of the Infant-school of St. George-the-Martyr,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184901010052"></xptr>
               <p>Southwark. At half-past ten on the night of 23d Nov., I fast<lb></lb>ened my shop-door, and went to bed; everything was then safe—at half-past six next morning, I found an entrance had been made into the shop by a small door having been forced open—I missed a coat and a hat—a cupboard had been forced open, from which I missed three pairs of scissors belonging to the Guardians, two waistcoats, a pair of trowsers, and a pair of Blucher boots—I saw the boots afterwards on the prisoner's feet; I am certain they are mine—the other things I have not seen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I bought them in Petticoat-lane for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
